                            <comment id="12588360" author="koji" created="Sun, 13 Apr 2008 05:54:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;How about this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. move firsrSearcher processing block from getSearcher() to a newly created private method&lt;br/&gt;
2. call the new private method at the end of SolrCore constructor&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12589699" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 20:13:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;firstSearcher should be called whenever a new searcher is being opened and there is no current searcher to base warming on.  Right now, that will only happen at startup, but in the future?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12589708" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 20:43:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW, applies cleanly and the tests pass.  As for the future, I guess I say we wait until it happens.  I can add a comment.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12589714" author="gsingers" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 20:59:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit this shortly.  Added to CHANGES and put in a comment about calls to firstSearcher initialization.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12589718" author="thyzz" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 21:09:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;there is a small typo in your patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;//TODO: It may not always be the case that this the only time the first searcher event needs to fire.&lt;br/&gt;
doFirstSearcherEvent(getSearcher().get());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;//TODO: It may not always be the case that this is the only time the first searcher event needs to fire.&lt;br/&gt;
doFirstSearcherEvent(getSearcher().get());&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12589961" author="gsingers" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2008 12:10:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 649046.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12593853" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 2 May 2008 20:19:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopening... This patch introduced a bug that prevents the first searcher opened from ever being closed.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m looking into a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12593864" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 2 May 2008 20:48:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is one possible (untested) fix.&lt;br/&gt;
I didn&apos;t test it because I&apos;m looking into something that might be a bit better.... just stall the executor until later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12593910" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 2 May 2008 23:00:35 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the latest version, which restores firstSearcher event handling to getSearcher, and uses a latch to block any searcher warming events until the end of the SolrCore constructor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12593960" author="koji" created="Sat, 3 May 2008 03:07:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I confirmed the fix. I like the second patch (uses a latch version). Thanks Yonik to solve this problem!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12594004" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 3 May 2008 16:44:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;fix committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
